    "## 1. Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "In the current 2026 economic climate, the American Dream of owning a home has shifted from a young adult's reality to an increasingly distant goal later in adulthood. While high housing prices are often blamed, the internal financial health of the average citizen — specifically their non-housing debt — can also act as a significant barrier.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project moves beyond simply examining whether individuals purchase homes and instead focuses on **when** they are able to do so. By quantifying the delay in homeownership caused by credit card balances, auto loans, and student debt, we aim to better understand the relationship between personal debt and major wealth milestones such as purchasing a home."
   ]
  },
